<sect2><title>libplot</title>
<para>
<command>libplot</command> is a C api which offers plotting functionality. With this library, you can write source code which using drawing primitives such as lines, circles, and so forth, and have the library turn this into a raster.
</para>

<sect3><title>Authors</title>
<para>
<command>libplot</command> is developed by Michael Still, and can be downloaded from http://www.stillhq.com
</para>
</sect3>

<sect3><title>Installation</title>
<para>
Follow these steps to install <command>libplot</command>
</para>

<execute><cmd>todo</cmd><input>Is this version number up to date?</input></execute>

<programlisting>
tar xvzf libplot_0_3.tgz
cd libplot-0.3
./configure
make
make install
</programlisting>

<para>
If you have installed <command>libplot</command> on an architecture / operating system combination which supports dynamic libraries, then you will need to run the <command>ldconfig</command> command or equivalent.
</para>

